President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated Gov. Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State as he marks 62 years. In a message to the Governor, released by his spokesman, Malam Garba Shehu, on Saturday in Abuja, President Buhari commended Sule for his “immense patriotism, hard work, and self-reliance to transform Nasarawa State to a land of peace, development and prosperity.”   The President commended the governor for the good governance in his tenure so far and wished that he would fulfil his dream of making Nasarawa State a peaceful and prosperous State, making it a model for others to copy. “May you stay healthy and live long, as you chart your very promising political career,” he said. (NAN)